This is a "plugin" for the Video Disk Recorder (VDR).

Written by:                  Andreas Regel <andreas.regel@powarman.de>

Project's homepage:          www.powarman.de

Latest version available at: www.powarman.de/vdr_plugins.htm

See the file COPYING for license information.

Description:
This plugin allows using a Griffin PowerMate to control some of VDR's functions
through the mapping of remote control keyss to PowerMate actions.

You can specify the PowerMate's device through command line parameter -d
(default:/dev/input/event0):

  vdr -P'powermate -d /dev/input/event1'

Setup Parameters
----------------
Brightness
    Sets the brightness of PowerMate's LEDs (0-255)
Sensitivity
    Sets the sensitivity of PowerMate's turning actions (1-10).
Use Pushed Turns
    Controls whether the pushed turn events should be used
Turn Left, Turn Right, Push Button, Pushed Turn Left, Pushed Turn Right
    The keys that should be triggered at the different events

